A RESOLUTION
1 Commending Margaret "Marjy" Stagmeier; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Margaret "Marjy" Stagmeier has long been recognized by her peers as a
3 community leader and champion of equitable housing who has dedicated innumerable hours
4 of her time and energy toward improving the lives of low-income families; and
5 WHEREAS, Marjy is a founding partner of TriStar, a nationally recognized real estate
6 investment firm based in Atlanta, where she led efforts to develop a sustainable housing
7 model that revitalizes marginalized apartment communities near underperforming elementary
8 schools; and
9 WHEREAS, this housing model has positively impacted over 10,000 families by creating
10 stable, affordable communities and fostering long-term neighborhood investment, thereby
11 helping to break cycles of poverty and build generational wealth through pathways to
12 home-ownership; and
13 WHEREAS, as additional testament to her dedication to the community, Marjy further serves
14 as the chair and founder of the nonprofit Star-C as well as the Advisory Board co-chair of
15 HouseATL; and
